UN Secretary General Kofi Annan expressed deep concern over Nepal's democracy after King Gyanendra dismissed the government and imposed a state of emergency.
The US, EU, Japan, and UK all condemned the king's actions and called for a return to democracy.
India aims to secure its border and maintain ties with Nepal.
China remained neutral, emphasizing Nepal's right to self-determination.
Gyanendra named a new Cabinet to restore democracy and peace talks with Maoists.
The international community urges Nepal to prioritize stability and democracy for the well-being of its people.
